article.headline: Robert Morris 83, Lafayette 70
article.story: EASTON, Pa. -- Jeremy Chappell scored 24 points to lead Robert Morris to an 83-70 victory over Lafayette on Wednesday night. Rob Robinson scored 15 points and Josiah Whitehead added 10 for Robert Morris (5-5), which built a 10-point halftime advantage and led by as many as 17 points in the second half. Andrew Brown scored a season-high 30 points for Lafayette (2-7). Jeff Kari added 12 points and Michael Gruner 11. Brown shot 7-for-11 from 3-point range and accounted for 21 of Lafayette's 36 first-half points.
